As you can see, I had a VERY serious, somber catch-up with my humorless friend, Taran Killam on the latest episode of “Life is Short” podcast 🧐
@tarzannoz, in addition to being tied for the nicest person in Hollywood (w his wife @cobiesmulders who is probably currently rolling her eyes), he’s also one of my favorite SNL cast members, a Broadway star (in Hamilton! Ever heard of it?!?) and, most importantly, the voice of my nephews favorite thing on earth @naturecatshow. He’s also an incredible impressionist - everyone from Brad Pitt to Michael Cera to LIS’s own @poodollar72! (aka “The Brad Pitt and Michael Cera of Podcasting”). 
I loved getting to catch up with him - hope you all do/did too (listen wherever you get your podcasts or swipe up in my stories!)

🎶“So hi, hi, Mr American Pie!”🎶 - #DonMcLame
@biggsjason (aka The menschiest of all mensches) is our guest on the latest episode of “Life Is Short” podcast (link in bio or story?)
Jason helped usher in the “teen movie boom” of the late 90’s/early 2000’s (to which I owe much of my own career) with a star-making performance in the now-classic movie “American Pie”. We talk about that, working on broadway in “The Graduate”, sobriety, his talented writer wife (@jennymollen) and that time he defecated in my toilet while it was being shown by my realtor and sent me photographic proof. Jason is, not only a Biggs talent, he also has a biggs heart and sense of humor - catching up with him was such a treat. I hope you all enjoy it too. P.s. I made chicken pot pie last night and only ate it - I know @biggsjason I’m such a prude! 🙄

